\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Could I have your name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Ivor. Ivor Short.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 5, Whitland Crescent, Fairwater.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 And you are married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, 1922.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 The year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 1901.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Landock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 In Glamorgan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I should - I - I - what I hears my mother talking about it my father I think it was about twelve month. Twelve - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Where did you go then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 To a place called the Tumble. Yes, that's just outside of Cardiff. This side of St Nicholas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 That's where you went to live from Landock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes. From Landock, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well - offhand I should say about two to three years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Where did you go then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 We moved then down to Ely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember the name of the place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 The Main Road, Cowbridge Road, Ely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You don't remember how long you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 A year or two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well - it could be two to three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember where you went then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I think we went to - Canton then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Remember the name of the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Albert Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Let me see now. How long was I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember why you moved from Landock to Tumble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 After my father's work. Yes, my father was a - a timber}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 man. And - he went now as a bailiff - for another farmer at - this side of St Nicholas. I think I - I - I think it was a Mr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734  Chip that used t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734 o have the big cab - all the cab}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
s and - he had the brakes you know for running around in, on the outings or weekends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Then you moved to Ely, was it because he changed his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I expect so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 And then you moved to Albert Street, do you remember why you moved to Albert Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I can't say why - why - why they moved.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I had three brothers and six sisters.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Could you give me the birth order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
There was May the oldest, born 1896. Elsie, 1898. Fred my brother 1900. Ivor 1901. Charles 1902, died infancy. That right? Louisa 1903. Edith 1904. Thomas 1905. Died infancy. Emily 1906. Nellie, 1910.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How old was your father when you were born? Thirty-six I think we worked out wasn't it? Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Bridgwater.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Somerset?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, Bridgwater, Watchet, Bridgwater.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What was his job there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Well I think his father - his relations had a farm there. And they lived in a place called - Schoolhouse, Watchet. He's still got relations there now somewhere. I haven't seen them for year and years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You don't know why he came over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I suppose like a good many more, for work. There was no work in - no work in them place in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What did he come over here to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I suppose he could get hold of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What job did he take, what was he doing when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well he was an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734 hauler}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734  when I were small. After he finished on the - farm work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did he have another job before or after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well he worked as a timber}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 man at Pontypridd in a pit. I know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Was that after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 That was after. Of course I - I can't recollect nothing about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What did he do after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Went back to his - back to doing his job he knew I suppose is as haulier.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 When he was living in Albert Street he was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734 hauler}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What did he actually have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well he - driving horses, timber, driving timber wagons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did he do any part time jobs or casual work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What did he do up to the end of the war, the first war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did he - what did he do in the first worl
d war? Up to the end? Oh he - he was working for a Bristol firm. And I think they was building the - the Town Hall, what we call the City Hall today. So they finished there and they went to build a new Co-op - in St Mary Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 So he was working as a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734 hauler}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734  all his life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, practically all his life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 When would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I can't say the exact date. But there was a - I could tell you this much. There was a bi
g meeting - big meeting in town. And - he went in central market, where the gates are, they - they went in there to have a speech - a talk about it, unemployment business. The police locked the gates, locked 'em in and went - went in and beat 'em up. Beca
use my father was one that was beat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You wouldn't remember when that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I can't say the date. There's a lot of unemployment at the time and there's a lot of trouble at the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Was it before the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 After the first world war. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You don't remember him being out of work before the first world war?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 When you were a little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, he was never out of work. No. Because he'd go miles to get a job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would he have his own trap or wagon or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well the only time he had the pony and tr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 p, when we lived up the Tumble - used to come round every Saturday, my mother and father, do the shopping in the Cardiff market. And we was little kiddies, all of us, we used to go in the house, lock
 and bolt the doors, and you stopped in there then 'til - one o'clock in the morning 'til my mother and father come home from the town. You dare not open that door, there's so many tramps about them days. Because my oldest sister got attacked by one of 'e
m In the lane on a Saturday night. Because it was only an old lane where we were living and one big house. And four small cottages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Oh good Lord, she was seventy -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Where did your mother come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
I think my mother - was a Cardiff woman. Yes, I think so, because my - my auntie - lived in Gough Street. And she'd been there all her life. That's all I - that's about all I can remember about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did your mother have any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. No, she had enough to do to look after us crowd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 My mother - was always on the milk round - before she was married, yes, she was telling me about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 So she did work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes. Before she was married, yes, on the milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Not their own business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, no, not their own business, working for somebody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What did she have to do, did she ever tell you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Deliver the milk. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 It was a horse and cart was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I should - I - I should think it'd be a horse and cart in them days. She -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 She didn't tell you about it, ever talk about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, she used to tell me about - what she used to do before she was married. And she was - she was telling me it was only - on
ly job she had was delivering milk in Cardiff. Because we were talking about old times in Cardiff and she was telling me all about it. I was interested in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What did she tell you,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Oh only about the times they had, and the works they had to do, and the hours they had to get up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What were they, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did she work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 She didn't do any part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You don't remember anything about the job she had, did she like it, delivering the milk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I suppose it's a job you either take or go without.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
I'd like to ask you about life at home when you were a child, this is up to the time when you left school, I think the house in Albert Street in Canton would be the ti
me wouldn't it, the time when you lived there. Do you remember what the house was like? How many rooms it had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 There was three up. Three up and a box room. Downstairs was the parlour and middle room and kitchen. And a small scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did anyone else besides your parents and your brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Before - that time, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Not when you were living there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, when we was living there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Was it a relative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Or a lodger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
It wasn't a rela - relative. I think my mother let - let a room for somebody. Yes, she let a spare - a spare room she had and a middle room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 The middle room downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did she let it to one person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, man and a - man and his wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 This is when you were a little boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, I can remember them because - he was a - she was a big tall woman, and a little short fellow. That's how I remember them two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Was it only the one couple?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, only the one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did your mother pay anyone to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 She never - they had no money to pay nothing in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did she do the washing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 She didn't send any washing out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. Had the boiler out the scullery, the clothes went in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would she do it all herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did your mother or father mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 All I can remember about that is my father doing all the boot mending. He mended all the boots and shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would your mother sew at all, make you clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did she mend the clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 She used to - well they had to mend them. If she didn't mend them we'd be naked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would your father ever mend them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I don't suppose so. He - he had to work hard enough all day, he was glad to rest at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would the clothes you had be new or would they be second hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I had a - one new suit I had. And the first time I wore it had a bloody good belting when I got home. For ripping it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
We went - we went up Leckworth, always went to Leckworth Sunday, you'd nowhere else to go. Went through some barbed wire - and ripped my - suit. When I gets home I gets a good hiding. The old Norforl
k suits. You wouldn't remember them would you? A Norfolk suit. It was a - stiff collar, hard - collar up here, with buttons down, and a belt. We used to call them the Norfolk suit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You remember having the one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Only one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How old would you have been then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 About ten Ireckon.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What did you have before, second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 hand or hand downs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Well - we couldn't get no hand downs because there was - we had no relations over you only my old - auntie, and she had no children. Her husband was a detective, in the City police.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You don't remember where your mother get your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. I expect she had 'em off the club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You don't remember where she'd buy your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Or when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about shoes, would you have new shoes or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Well we'd - as far as I can recollect we had new shoes. But every time they wanted do you couldn't afford to send them to the cobbler. My father used to do all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about lighting the fire in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. Well he used to go out very early in the mornings so there was no need to light the fire that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about cleaning the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Always spotless.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would your father help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Cooking?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 My mother used to do all the cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Not your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about washing up, would your father help with the washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well the - the girls had to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about repairs around the house, would your father do any repairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well the - of course I can't say anything about that. I can't recollect nothing about the repairs and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember whether he ever dressed you, your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 He might have put a napkin on me, I don't know about anything else. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Undressing you, or bathing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 We used to bath in the big bath in front of the fire, one after the other. Like - like - like a lot of sheep going in the dip.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would he help to bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I expect so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would he ever read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would he ever tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would he take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Yes. I remember him taking me out - we lived up the Tumble in the country - and he said to me - he took me to - Cardiff in the pony and trap, and we finished up in a place called the Palace, which they call the Hippodro
me today, now it's shut. And I remember - I remember that because a thing I never forget. It was cowboys and Indian on the stage. And half time used to have little bioscope pictures, little small one in the middle half time. And all the - people up the ga
l
lery used to bring out their bottles of beer. And if there's any - any noise downstairs they'd drop their bottles on 'em. And that's not - that's not - fancy, I was there and seeing it. I mean that - that's a thing I should never forget. The first time th
at ever I went to - a Palace of Varieties.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Was it only you with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Only me and my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Not any of the other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did he ever look after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I don't think my mother ever went o
ut. I can remember my mother - when I was about five - might be a little earlier - working in the field - planting cabbage. And me and my brother going along in front - marking out and dropping 'em so she's come along with a peg. That's when my father was
 - working for - a farmer called Arthur Morgan, at Wendal. And to get - to try to get extra few shillings she used to go out and work on the - planting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 And she used to take you children with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, we used to live on - we - our house was on the corner, and the - the garden - big garden's at the back of the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Now how long did she do that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well about three - as far as I can reckon about three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Not all the time I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, not all the time, only in the planting season.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 When you were a little boy did you have any jobs that you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You didn't do anything around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You didn't have to clean the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Nothing like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about after you left school, did you have any regular jobs then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well, I left school - I left school just after thirteen and a half. And - I started now - with my father. Well my father did - I went to 
this man for a job, he said, can you drive horses, I said, yes, I was brought up with them. All right he said - start right away. So when I come in in the night time - who is in the - who is the shed but my father. He asked me what I was doing there. I sa
i
d, I was driving that big horse over there. He said, you're not driving that. I said, I am driving that. I - what are you doing? I said, I'm hauling bricks I said from the brickyard row down to Victoria Park. Of course there was no houses at Victoria Park
 
then, it was all spare ground, orchards. From there on I - before I was fourteen I was in lodgings. A place called Pontlodin. We went up - we went up there and cleared three hundred acres of timber to - sink a new PD - a new shaft for a - for the PD, coal
 people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Powell Duffryn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You had to go and live there then did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, no. I was lodgings then. In a caf\'e9.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Just while you were on the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did you come home at the weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. Every fortnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How long were you doing the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 About 1914 to 1917.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You had three years in lodgings?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Yes, I used to - we used to travel different places clearing timber. Well I - well I was driving three horses then, not one. Three in what they call a single chain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 So you didn't really do any jobs around the house to help your mother and father at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
No, well the only - the only way I could help my mother and father was by - delivering milk first thing in the morning before I went to school - and working as barbers boy at night time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 But you didn't do any jobs around the house, in the actual home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about your brothers and sisters, did they help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I know my brother didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I couldn't say off hand about the girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You don't remember them doing any jobs around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. My mother was very strict with them thought. Oh yes. Mother was strict - was strict with all of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about you older children, did you help the younger children to dress or eat or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Well, no, I don't think so. You can - when we went to - when we moved to the Tumble - we didn't have much time for anything, because we used to have to walk home and
 to school. And four miles back. And you had to go whether it was that high with - six foot of snow, you still had to go. You - you didn't have much time to do anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about when you lived in Albert Street? Did you do any jobs around the house then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 None of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time when you were in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You don't remember what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. When my father and mother said bed you went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did your mother put you to bed or anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Mother. My mother always put us to bed, mother always looked after us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember at what age you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did you share the bedroom with anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, my - with my brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 That would be Fred?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did you share a bed with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You don't remember now how the sleeping arrangements were, you had three bedrooms? In the house in Albert Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 We had a - in - in - in the House in Albert Street - my
 mother and father - slept in the - the back room. So many of my sisters slept in the middle room. And in the big - front bedroom - there was - a partition, well me and my brothers used to have a bed in one side, and my youngest sisters on the other side.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Was it you and Fred that were in the bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes. And my youngest sisters were in - it was in the other side of the other partition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 In the living room.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
 every}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 time you was dirty I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You didn't bath once a week, you bathed more often than that did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 When we - when we got old enough - to go into town, we used to go to Guildford Crescent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 To the baths, the public baths?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How old would you be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I'd say about nine or ten. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 While you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 But before then would you all bath in turn? Would the girls bath with the boys or after one another or what would the arrangements be?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 The - they had a big bath in the kitchen by the fire. You'd got nowhere else to go. Well they used to line up, take your turn and out.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Where would the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You never remember eating in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
No. We had - we had the parlour but that was - in them days a parlour was a parlour you weren't even allowed in there. Unless you was courting. Well the middle room was - the girls room. And we had the kit - we was in the kitchen for our meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Where did your mother cook?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 The biggest part of her cooking in the oven. In the range.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 She didn't have a gas cooker did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, there was a gas cooker there, very very old one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 In Albert Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What room was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 In the scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did she use the gas cooker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 And the range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 She had two cooking stove really then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well before you went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Can you remember back to breakfast in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, you can't very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would you all be having breakfast together, or would your father have gone out to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well it - it - it was the same then as it is - as it is today. You had to grab as you can - could and get to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would you sit down at a table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You would have to sit down. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How many of the family would be there now having breakfast with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Well - some of us had to go a long way to school. Me other brother had to go - from Albert Street to Virgil Street. Well that's a - we'd be up first because my sisters only had to go down the street, to the National school. On - that's just I on t
he corner. It meant that we had to be up an hour before them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 So you and your brother would have breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Fred and you, and then your mother would be giving you breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Oh my mother'd be up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would she be having breakfast with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes. No, she'd have - wait and have hers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about your father, he'd already had his breakfast had he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, he used to carry his food out. Breakfast and dinner. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 He wouldn't have anything in the morning before leaving the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 He might have a cup of tea. And his pipe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would your mother get up with him then to get him off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I can always remember cutting his food the night before. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember what you had to eat and drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well - we didn't have cornflakes, none of this fancy stuff}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 they sell today. What we used to have, whatever it was it was solid. And you knew you'd had it when you'd had it, you got - knew you'd had a meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You don't remember what it was you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. There'd be no such thing as beans on toast and - all this - cereal they've got today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What would you have to drink then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Ordinary tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about Sunday or any other day, would you have the same breakfast?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 We used t
o - on - on a Sunday - we used to have to take our syrup and treacle, that was the start. If you didn't have your syrup and treacle - you had no breakfast. So you had to have it. Or - senna pods. Of course - every Sunday regular. And you get up, have a bi
t of breakfast then go up Leckworth. Because - we used to go to church now and again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about midday meals now, when you went to school when you were living in Albert Street, would you come home dinner time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Come home dinner time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would you have your dinner then or would you have sort of a snack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Have a dinner. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You don't remember what sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well a cooked meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What time would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 About half past twelve to one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How many members of the family would be having dinner then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well all of us I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Not your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, he wouldn't be home, he were working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What would you have to eat then, and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well a - same as you get today, ordinary cooked dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 After you had your dinner you'd have a glass of water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about the other meal of the day, would you have an evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You'd have your tea, the same as - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What would you have for tea?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I don't - you - you've go
t a job to say, you can't bring your memory back to that extent what you - you - what you had to eat. See, you have your tea, you never think about - tomorrow what you've had yesterday do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What do you think you had to eat in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well
 our Sunday dinner - we never had meat. My mother and father used to have the meat, we used - and they - we used to have the gravy. On our dinner. And if they couldn't afford to buy it - and my father used to say there's more nutriment in the gravy than w
hat's in the meat. And she'd make her own brawn with the - pigs heads and that. What they get in the butchers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would you have an evening meal in the week, you had tea, what would you have for tea
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I should think it was mostly Maypole margarine, you bought a pound they give you a pound. Or bread and jam. Or some cakes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would you have a meal again then before going to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Only tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You wouldn't have - even have a cup of tea. Nothing. You had your tea and that was your lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember having different food on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Oh yes, yes. I - oh these big jam tarts. Don't turn it on yet. Things were very hard and - there's a lot of trouble down the docks. I believe the railwaymen was out}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 on strike. And we couldn'
t get coal, couldn't get fire for love nor money. So there was - me and my pals - seven of us, coming home from school - the older men was throwing coal on the road off the trucks. Seven of us got caught. I was only just about ten or eleven. We was taken 
to the court for stealing six}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
pen'orth of coal. And they had no option, they give us three strokes of the birch, some had six. For stealing six}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
pen'orth of coal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Can you tell me more about this? What did it feel like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well it - it's an awful experience. It's a thing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734 
you never forget. And it's a pi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 ty they didn't bring it back today. There wouldn't be so much crime if there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What did you think at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well being young - inexperienced - we thought it were going for the birthday. A
nd when we got to court I can remember when we got to court - all of us laughing and joking, never thought how serious - 'cos they take it serious. And when he took us in this big cell - down the law courts - 'til after dinner, they called us in - in this
 other room one at a time and - I had three, my brother had three, and the two older - older - the two oldest had six strokes a piece.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Was it a cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, a birch. That's a thing I never forgot. And I don't think my pals ever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What did your father and mother say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Well they couldn't say nothing. It isn't like if you carry a hundred weight of coal. If you had a lump on your hand about six - cost about - it - it wouldn't be sixpence in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would she bake it at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Home, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 In the oven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes. All her - all her}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 own cake. Rice puddings, everything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would your father bake bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I don't think so. Because them you was always out working, and you had to work, in them times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would your mother make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would she bottle fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 She'd do anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did she make any wine?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Any medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. Is it? Small beer used to call it, but I don't know what they call it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Ginger beer was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Herb beer. Made of the nettles. Yes. Ah.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You don't remember how she made it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Like - like boiling cabbage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 With nettles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, and nettles, you drain it off and - I suppose you let it ferment then, put something with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would she make any beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 She wouldn't brew any beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did your mother or father grow their own vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. The only time - we had vegetables and fruit is when he - when he was on the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 That's when you were very small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Very small, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about in Cardiff when you were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 in Albert Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, we had no garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did they buy any vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, they used to have to buy - as far as I can reckon day to day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would they buy any fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
I expect so. They used - used - they used to get a lot of barrows coming round them days. Barrow boys they call 'em today but - they used to come round in their droves that time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember eating fruit when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would you have tinned vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I don't know if there was such thing as tinned vegetables then was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 There was tinned fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Tinned fruit, not vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did you ever have tinned fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Never?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
There used to be a big shop in Canton, big fruit shop - called by the name of A.D. Davis. And they used to get - they used to have a sale every Saturday,
 sell out, they used to go down and - they used to go down and buy it like. Same as the market, always sale day Saturday. You go in the market, my mother and father used to go in the market - the fish place, and they'd enough fish for the week for about a
 shilling
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You'd have a lot of fish would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Yes. You'd buy so much and they'd give you so much. I forget the name of the fish No. Bream. They used to get the bream for nothing. They'd buy a - hake - a big long hake about two foot long, I don't 
know how much it cost but they used to get two or three breams thrown in with it. I can remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did you keep any livestock, like hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, my father kept - fowls. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Who looked after the hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 My father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Only your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You wouldn't have anything to do with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. I used to keep rabbits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 To eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 To eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You'd look after those would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Or your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Me and my brother like out the - out the back. We used to let them run wild in the back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 So you got extra meat from rabbit, you never poached?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, I did. I used to have a greyhound. A greyhound - and a terrier. I used to go up the woods - sit on
 the bridge and send the two dogs into the wood. The terrier would roust them out and the old - greyhound would catch them and bring them over to me. I couldn't cross the bridge because - if I did the police'd have me. Because there were - there were poli
ce from another area. So I used to stop on one side of the bridge and let the dogs go in and do the trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Where would you be getting them from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Leckworth. Leckworth Wood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Two or three times - we used to live up there, two
 or three times a week we used to go up, but - if you wanted the boys you always went up Leckworth, don't matter whose boys they were. That's the only playing field they had, or playing ground. It was common ground. Of course - it's only now lately the Co
rporations took it over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How often would you go out for the rabbits?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Every chance I had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How often would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Perhaps - it might be seven days a week. Well you wouldn't catch 'em every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 So that would be a help to your mother then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes. Oh a big help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How many times a week would you have meat in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Well my mother always kept a stockpot. Same as the wife's mother always kept a stock - what they call a - a stockpot on the - the range. And there was a
lways meat in that. We didn't all - we didn't always have it. 'Cos we used to do with the rabbits and my father used to go for the gun with the hare - get these hares. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How often would he shoot hares?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well - if he cold get up to this certain
 place, he was allowed to shoot them. But I say it's like a good many more, he didn't have chance to get up there, no buses running up there, nothing like that, you had to walk miles and miles. There was no benefit going up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 But he would go occasionally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 He kept a gun, he always had a gun?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, well not a - not - for years he hadn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 But when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 So you would occasionally have a hare?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well we might get a pheasant or two, if you - if you didn't get caught. You -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Can you remember having it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Yes, I can. I can remember - I had a couple of pheasants myself, and I got caught Yes, I - I had a damned good hiding off the gamekeeper and told to go home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How are you going}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734  to catch the ph}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 easants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
I catch 'em all right. You get a bag - you get a - a sweet bag, the old fashioned sweet bag, put a bit of lime in the bottom - and put a couple of - couple of corn in there. And the pheasant would put his head 
in the bag and he couldn't see after. You could go to catch him then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 But you'd have to lie in wait for it would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. Didn't have to lie and wait. You had to get a certain way away. Or another way they used to do it was - in the night time w
hen the pheasant roost in the tree they put a flashlight on it, and blind them. They cant see where they are. Of course you don't do it today because you get jail for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 It was a common thing then was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes. There used to be a lot of chaps up
 there - well men they were, they'd be - using slings. And they use them slings like a man uses a rifle. Because what they aim with that sling, they knew they were going to hit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How many times would you have meat in a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I can't say offhand. All according to what mother had in the pantry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would you ever have tinned meat, like corned beef?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I expect so. But you wouldn't be able to buy a tin, they were all big tins in them days wasn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you ever remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, not as I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did your father have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well he only had his ordinary rations to go to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Were you allowed to talk during the meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. Nor read.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked, or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 If you didn't put - if you didn't eat what - what was put on the table, you went without. And you had nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well you had no need to. You had no need to ask for a second helping. Because you you had enough - when you went for your meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 If there was something on the table that you wanted, like the salt, would you ask somebody to pass it to you
 or would you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I don't suppose them times you bothered about it because everything was put in your food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I'm very much afraid there was very little left on the plate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well you picked - you picked it up as - by watching your parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did you have to sit in a certain way at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You had to sit at the table in a proper manner. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
It's all according - what you mean by toys. What are they? What, at Christmas and all the things we had for twelve months - was a sixpenny stocking. And when you opened it there was nothing in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You wouldn't have anything in the Christmas stocking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 There was hardly anything in it, but these lot of old papers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 So you wouldn't have toys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. No. If you had a ha'penny a week for your pocket, you was lucky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 When could you leave the table at the mealtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Oh after meals.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 When you finished could you leave or did you have to wait 'til your mother told you
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, you could leave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You didn't have to wait for the others to finish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 When you had your food you could get up and go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You'd get up, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 All I know - all I could recollect now was - my mother had a long bench - one side of t
he table, two chairs the other side, and one on each end. I don't - I think she had a - used to get a tin opener to put us in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would your father sit one end and your mother the other or how would they sit now round the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No - my brother and father would always have it after. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Your father and your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 My father and my mother used to have it after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 On their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, with the other -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 They never ate with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, they - they - well they had no room on the table. And used to have a bit of peace to have theirs after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did you always sit in the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember now how you sat round the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, it's as I say, there was five or six one side. On this long bench. The
re was a table that end, table that end, there was two table - chairs - one each end and two this side. That's all I could recollect about that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How was the meal served? Would your mother serve it out in the scullery and bring it in on the plates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, on the table. Used to bring it all in on the table. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 On the plates ready.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes. All - tureens. Or pots, whatever they used to and they used to put the plates out - out at - put all the dinners together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Dish it out on the table in the living room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What order would she serve you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I couldn't say offhand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Who would she give the plate to first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 God knows, I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Where would the younger brothers and sisters sit before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, I don't remember nothing about that. No. No. No. In fact - in fact I haven't seen my sisters - twenty-one years I've seem my sisters.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about when they were little when you were children, you don't remember them much as babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. All I can remember them is going to the - National school. That's about all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well to some of us. My father his favourites, my mother 
had her favourites. I was mother's favourite. My brother - oldest brother was my father's favourite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How did you know you were the favourite?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well - I'm not that stupid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How did she show it I mean?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Oh - different ways of showing it. Every mother got her favourite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 And your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes. Well I - I didn't agree with it myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 If you had any worries could you share them with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I never had worries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about your father, could you go and talk to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Well, if - if I was out playing - like out the street - as young boys, if I got into trouble and a bloke smacked me one I went into my father and told him he'd tell me to get outside and give the bloke a hiding or he'd give me one. So he said, that
'll be two you'll have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I never had no more stricter parents than what any - anybody had. My mother with me - since I've}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid613474\charrsid1851734  been married. For giving my che}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 ek. And I wouldn't have none of my brothers nor sisters answer my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 My father said, if you can't fight your own battles don't come to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Mother was the same. There'd be no row - there'd be no rows over children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well that chance did they have? What chance did they have to be anything in them days If you h
ad the brains you couldn't get on. Because there was such a thing as the old school tie, ie. He was a gentleman's son - or you went to university, you was - you wasn't recognised, you was only a common labourer. Because - it didn't matter what brains you 
h
ad in school - the same thing applied in school, if you went to school with a collar and tie you was it. Like I - I do remember that. And you went to school, you were a couple of minutes late you had a damned good hiding, for being a couple of minutes lat
e, no fault of your own. Perhaps your mother got up too late or something like that, that particular morning. They used to beat the living lights out of you then. In school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Who would beat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Headmaster. I could picture him now. Mr Nettleden the - headmaster.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 With a cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Too true with a cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 On your hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, on your hands. Three on each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 For being late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, you couldn't feel your hands all day}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid613474\charrsid1851734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
No, I think - I say after I left school I didn't wait 'til I was fourteen. I had to get out and earn some money. And from that - that's when - from that day on I had to - fend for myself. If anything went wrong I had to do it 
- do it myself. I wasn't afraid of work, I never have been afraid of work. And I could go anywhere to work. I worked with my father, I just said well - being on my own out - out in the desert somewhere for all - all he - taught me like, or like were willi
ng to teach me was nothing. He was too - full of his own work, he couldn't afford to give you the time to do it. And the bosses then wanted their shillings}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4666256\charrsid1851734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 worth out of you. He did - they didn't - they didn't want your flesh, they wanted the bones and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What did your mother and father think about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Never knew what swearing was. We used to - had to go to the Memorial Hall, church. If you didn't go - and show the starred card - you had another belting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 From your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Both of 'em. One that was - one that was most handy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 When the grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. We used to get a - these - kiddies - boys - boys books you know, the Marvel and what they used to call
 it, something else, and we used to - father used to pay the devil because we used to read 'em and look at the pictures. Used to call it rubbish But it proved different today, haven't it, oh it's all come true.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You weren't allowed to join in to talk with the grown ups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 If you did something that your parents didn't like, disapproved of, what would happen
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well they'd teach you a lesson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 If your mother said yes and you said no that was your lot. You never said no again. And you had to be in them days. You had to be strict.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Why did you think they had to be strict then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Well - at them times - there was no pictures - there was no pictures, no television, no big dance halls - all I can remember I - all I can rem}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4666256\charrsid1851734 ember about town is the old ska}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
ting rink. Where they used to - hold the boxing contests, Jimmy Well and - Freddy Wells, Frank Moran and all them. And the show grounds in Wood street. And we had a big - circus come here from Australia in 1911. The biggest e
ver known been in Cardiff. Remember Bill Cody coming here, the cowboy. With all his Indians. That's all you had to look forward to. And you never had the money, used to go in there, we used to slip in. Underneath the tent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 If you were punished by your parents who would punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Mother or father. I'd sooner have it off my mother though. Aye, she were lighter handed than what he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How would they punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 My father had a belt. And you'd get a few of them. And you'd know you had i
t after because it'd mark you. He wouldn't bruise you nor nothing but - it showed in wheals. My mother had a cane always, a cane hanging up. And you dare not touch the cane off that hook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How often would you be punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Every time you done wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How often would that be?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Oh it wouldn't be very often. Because - of a weekend - we wouldn't be in the house really, only mealtimes, we'd be out. I've seen us get up Sunday morning, walk to Barry Island. Walk home again. Couldn't afford the f
are for the train. I don't know how much it was then, about tuppence or three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4666256\charrsid1851734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
pence then to go to Barry, Barry Island. We used to get up, perhaps wrap some sandwiches up me mother, be off then, walk to Barry Island. Come back over Leckworth Bank. We'd be o
ut all day. Then when the - sometimes after when they opened the football ground, Ninian Park, we used to go over there and watch them then. But always spent our time up Leckworth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Yes. Me and me brother was - getting at loggerheads. And my mother put him his dinner. And he said - he started showing off, he didn't want it, he wasn't going to eat that. So I told him, I said, Fred, I said, if you don't stop cheek - cheeking your mothe
r, I said, I'll belt you own. So - my father got to hear of it, and he took us out the back, now, he said, the two of you get on with it. So - I was always a bit stronger than Fred. So he got the worst end of the stick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You fought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Your father watching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Yes, out the back watching. Seeing there was fair play. Well one thing boiled down to another and now he's waiting outside the door with his coat off. I walked away. He kept on and on and on 'til I had to - me and him had to ha
ve it. So by beating him I - I got beat by the old man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How did he beat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Corporal punishment, the same - the same as - same as any other boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Oh we used to - laugh it off. Laugh it off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 It didn't worry you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. We used to have our little gangs going about - every street had a little gang. We was always fighting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Who would you be figh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4666256\charrsid1851734 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 ing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Oh, chap from another gang. Take you on the spare ground. Be nothing of - Sunday morning - or Sunday afternoon - that's our amusement.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You didn't feel bitter or anything about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would you say you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Or did one of them play more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, they were both the same. I say a little bit towards my mother. Out of the two my mother was the best really, I speak honestly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 In what way do you feel that she was the best?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well - a woman always got more feeling ways than a man. Where a woman could sit down and think things over a man can't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well, we was only talking about that yesterday. You never knew what a birthday was. Y
ou'd never know what a birthday card was. All you'd know, it's - it's your birthday tomorrow and it was forgot after. All you were waiting for 'til you was fourteen so you can go to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did you receive any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did you have anything special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No visitors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember Christmas Day, doing anything with your mother or father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 We always had our Christmas dinner Christmas Day, same as anybody else. But you never had the things they - they get today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What did you have for Christmas dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Oh God knows. Oh I expect it was chickens because father always kept fowls. And I followed my father that way, I always kept fowls. Didn't I?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You don't remember doing anything specially on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would it be any different from another day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. Not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No different Christmas Day from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 My father used to - play the accordi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4666256\charrsid1851734 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 n. And the flute. Yes.
