\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Where would they see their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well around you know like they - round - people living around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did they share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well they always had the same friends because they - people didn't move them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would your mother have friends now of her own, different friends from your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. They was all pals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would your father have friends of his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
My father never went out. What I mean he - he - he never made a habit of paling up with anybody. But he - they all - they always acknowledged anybody. The same as me, I don't worry about nobody. But - everybody speak.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would any friends be invited into your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Not as I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You never remember any coming in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You never remember anybody coming in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Not to have anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did anybody call in casually into your home without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would neighbours come in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Oh neighbours, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would they have to wait for an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would they knock and come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Knock at the door, knock the door and come in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How often would they come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well they only really lived two doors, next to and next door and next - they were all neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would you have neighbours coming in every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Any trouble they - everybody'd be there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did your parents ever go out like that to neighbours houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would they go out of an evening or would your mother go in the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well as far as I can - as far as I can go back my father had to stop i
n while mother went for hour with her friend - to the pictures. I don't ever remember seeing my mother in a public house, or heard about her being in a public house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 When your father would go to the pub would he have any special friends to go with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Well the trouble with my father, he used to drink on the way home from work. He never - he'd never go out after. He - he might go out - he might come home Saturday and might go for an hour Saturday night. But the - the - the troub - that was the tr
ouble in them days. The men used to have their beer before they come home, after they - after they finished work used to go in the pub. Of course they was open all day then. You could go in - you could go in a cafe then - and get rum and coffee and all th
at sort of thing. And the - public houses open all day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
People often say now that in those days they made their own amusements, what do you think your parents did when they went in with their friends or with their neighbours? Would they make music or play games?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Oh yes. They'd have music out the street. Yes. Used to play the accordian and that - did a dance out the street. Yes. Yes, I think so.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in the time before 1918 did yo
u think of some people belonging to one class and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well as far as I - as far as I can gather there was two classes of people. The working class and the upper class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What class would you say you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 To the lower class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What sort of people belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well, the majority of working people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What sort of people belonged to the other class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well - it's the same as the - what can I say, it's the same as the Tory party and L
abour party. All the world over. What the upper class had they held. What - what the lower class had they had to fight for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Were you ever told to touch your cap or to show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well you never wore a cap in them days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You'd never touch your head, or would your sisters curtsey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Was there anybody you would call sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes In school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Anybody master?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No master.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Anybody'd you'd call madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents by touching their cap or calling them sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I can't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 In the district where you lived who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Well I think they were all classed the same near enough in the area where I lived. There were no upper class living there at all. Of course you had the shopkeepers, you - you - you - they were they same as yourself. All these
 little shops - only get a living out of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 There was no one in the area that you considered more important than anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 So you didn't come into contact with any of the upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, it was - it was a kind of two areas. 
And one a working class area and one a middle class area. So very rare you went down that way. Oh there was Riverside A place called Riverside, that was a Jewish quarter. Practically all Jews. And it's very rare you went down that way, unless you was goin
g to school the long way around. And the - Theatre Road was all upper class people. That}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244156\charrsid1851734 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
s where the big houses are. Around Landeth Fields.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would you ever come into contact with the middle and upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Not in - not in the young days, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Why do you think they were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well they - they were the moneyed people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about the shopkeepers, who would they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 With anybody as long as they could sell their goods.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about the clergy or the ministers, did you come into contact with any of them? Who would they mix up with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Well I - I never remembered one coming to the house. No. Not that is - it's not not like it is today, they come and visit in the house and - all that, but you - they never - I don't think they done it in them days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 The only contact with the minister is if you went to church on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well the teachers were good as long as you was good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would they be living near where you were living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would you have any contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, they'd be living outside - I remember the - the teachers where I was going to school lived outside of Cardiff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Who would they associate with, who would they be friendly with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well they'd be friendly with everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 There were no farmers were there around where you were living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about the employers, who would they mix with, or associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well all the - all the - all the big firms
, I say big firms, they'd only docks, and outside of Cardiff. There wasn't many firm - there wasn't many working places in - inside of Canton, only one, the Canton Saw Mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 So you wouldn't come into contact really with any employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 It was just a working class district of houses for working class people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Houses, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well everybody. It was - what can I say - you was made to go to church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Who would make you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Your parents would make you. Of course in my case I had to. I didn't want to go but I had to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You had to go on a Sunday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, and they used to have a - had to prove we went to church we used to have a little book, and they used to
 stamp a star in there. So when you went home you'd to - you had to show your mother and father your star as you'd been to church. Or admit I hadn't been in recent years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 We're talking about now when you were in school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Church of England then you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Was there a chapel around then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 A chapel, now let me see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You did mention a Salvation Army, would they have had a mission where you were living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, they had a small mission behind the church now I recollect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Who would be going to the Salvation Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Oh the youngsters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You don't recall a chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 A nonconformist chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. No, I can remember the Brunel Street Church. St Carrick's church in Welsh Street. The Band of H
ope, where was the Band of Hope? No, the Band of Hope was opposite the Royal Oak. By Woolworth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244156\charrsid1851734 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 s. That big church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, they're all the same. It was all working class people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did they live the same sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Same way. I knew biggest part of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 They weren't different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, just - of course there were some had better jobs than others the s
ame as is today. They had a bit more money but - we all lived the same. You couldn't afford to live any different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you think that any group in the working class felt superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you think some families were thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well there was some rough ones. And they were brought up rough. I wasn't brought up rough but I was brought up the hard way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 When you say brought up rough what do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well allowed to do as they like. Some rough people. Yes. You always had troublemakers don't matter where you went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would some be thought of as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Everybody was respectable. Respect and respected, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember a distinction between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244156\charrsid1851734 Well you a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
lways had that distinction. There was always class distinction. Ever since I can remember there was class distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you think there was a difference in the working class between the craftsmen and the people who were labouring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Well there was always that bit of edge. With the craftsmen. But I don't suppose I made any difference when they were working together. That's all you - I was always treated - when I started work, treated with respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, I suppose so. There was - there was no restrictions stop you moving anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember anybody who did move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, was all - all - if you moved you'd go in the same area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I mean moving from the working class to the middle class of upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. I suppose you could if you had the means.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What would the means be do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well - a better class of wage, a better class of living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember anybody described as a real gentleman? Or a real lady in those days
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 We was never without them. No. And they were policemen in them days. As long - as long as you was six foot six - and about twenty sto
ne he was a policeman. But I can say this about them. They never run to court if - if you done anything wrong They'd take you home. See your parents and give you a damned good hiding in the street. My father - my father was a big friend of Inspector King'
s in Canton police station. But it didn't make a bit of difference. I still had - still had my cane across my backside. Not only me, but everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What would he give you the cane for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well for - doing something you shouldn't do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Well - they all though well of Inspector - Inspector King. But he was - he was dead you were dead afraid of - if you're doing anything wrong of seeing the policeman. He wasn't brutal. But sooner than take you to court or anything - mi
sdemea - anything wrong you know, very slight, anything like that, he'd have the choice of having a hiding - or you'd have the choice of having his cane. And I've seen six or seven of us lined up in the street, having our hiding, off the policeman.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Were you sort of frightened of him, did your mother ever say I'll call a policeman if you were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How do you think the policemen then treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well - the same as they do today. You had to behave yourself. But the mo
st - the mostly cases I can remember is people being drunk and disorderly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Was there a lot of that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Yes, there was. I see'd them on a Saturday night, drunk, laying in the roads, and the police have had to get the hand truck and take 'em down on a hand truck.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 That was the most was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Yes. I remember one murder in Canton. The Binden - that was the Binden murder, by the Canton police station. Oh you was like - every other schoolboy, we was always in - up to devilment. And you might 
go a bit too far. And that was your lot You'd get the fatherly advice off him. But it was nothing - there was nothing - I was going to say there was nothing wrong with 'em. They was there to do their job
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did you ever see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
The landlord was Mr Bale of Llanduth. He owned the three houses. And we used to see him every Monday morning. With his old pony and cart. Sometimes he had the rent and sometimes he didn't. So you had to pay the fortnight after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well - since I've grown up - we was friends. The best of pals. And I was speaking to him just before he died. Over here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about when you were a child, what did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well he didn't - he - you took no notice of him then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 But you knew he came on a Monday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes. But you had no interest in it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Struggle? Struggle wasn't t
he word. You had to struggle on the wages you got. Well - well - it only proves, the public'll prove it today, they've had a struggle to live today. I've heard people talk about the good old days, they'd like to go back to the good old days. There's many 
a
 thousand wouldn't. Because I don't think he knows anything about the good old days or they wouldn't be - wouldn't be so fond of shouting about it. You had to go - go back to the good old days if you had the money behind you. When you had the - when you h
a
d the coal owners in Wales, you had the coal owners in England, they made their million. They'd like to go back to the good old days when men were slogging their guts out in the pits for nothing. That's why - that's the people that wants the good old days
. They was making a fortune out of the - out of the working class. But you know that now don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What did you think about it, the fact that your parents had to struggle so much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well you couldn't do nothing about it then, you didn't think of it at that time. But you've had time to think since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 But did you fe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244156\charrsid1851734 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 l as a little boy that they were having a struggle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well no, you didn't - you didn't look at it to that extent. You wasn't old enough really to know anything about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I don't - I can't recollect my father being ill at all. Only just - three months before he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Was he ever out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 There was a - not when I was a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You don't remember when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 He was never out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. But you had to travel about to get work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did you ever have to get help from the Guardians or the parish or any charity?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I don't think at all about that when I - not when I was a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You don't remember it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 When there was someone in the district where you lived whom the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they 
showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Well, only think I could re - recollect - about that - was some coloured people come and they live - in the same street. And it's as that is there. They had 'em out. Yes. They wouldn't have coloured people in the street, I could - I could 
picture the man now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How did they do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Had 'em evicted. Out. Yes. And that was in a street called Chancery Lane. Close by. And that is the truth that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Were you ever given lessons by one of your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You went to school, how old were you when you first started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I think I was five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What time of the morning did you go when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well, school used to start at nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 When did you come back then, when you first started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Dinner times. Oh just a minute, when I started school was - in St George's. And we used to - have to take sandwiches with us for dinner. Yes. From the Tumble, to - the - this side of St Nicholas, to St George's the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What time would you come back from there in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well - in the winter you used to leave school about four o'clock. I should think. To walk back home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What kind of a school was it, was it a Church school or the Board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, Board school, ordinary mixed - little mixed school - it - it - yes, it's there today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 About three quarters of an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Me and my brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Fred?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 And - my older sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 May and Elsie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You had your midday meal in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What did you have to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Sandwiches.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What would they be of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Oh God know now, I couldn't tell you. Never had no tea. Only water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What did you think of school, that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well - I never thought much of school any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You went from there then didn't you, from that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Because you moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Canton.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 That would be still the infants school you'd go to in Canton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How far did you have to walk then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well you know the little street don't you? We used to go to Virgil Street school then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Quite a long}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6244156\charrsid1851734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
way then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would you come home dinner hour then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What time would you start school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 And you'd come back what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 We used to come home to dinner. Go back again. And then come home again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Was that a mixed school? Or boys only?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Boys - boys only. Girls downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Who went with you to school there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Nearly all the Canton boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How long would it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well about half an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You went home for your midday meal, what did you think of school there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Not - speaking candidly, not much.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Well if you didn't go - if you didn't learn a lot you had to go. If you didn't go you went to Borstal. Well - Brynadon. You know where Brynadon is don't you, that's where they used to send you if you didn't go to school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did you have to go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, I was threatened to go there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You didn't go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did you dislike school, or did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I didn't like school. No, I speak candidly, I didn't like school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Pretty good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You liked them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Of course they were led by the headmaster. Any punishment the headmaster gave it to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No, I think they - they - all they were interested was learning. Reading, writing and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I can't recollect that either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well you all - you had to be tidy to go to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 And the same thing applies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 What about the way you spoke, did they bother about that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 If you did something the teachers disapproved of? What would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well you'd get the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Would the girls be punished the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Well I couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Because you were in a boys school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You don't remember your sisters saying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 For what would you have to do now to be punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 
Well you either be late for school - or you done something - some - something wrong. That displeased the teachers or the headmaster, then you was taken out to the hall and - given a good caning. In front of the whole school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Where would you have the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Across the hands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 In front of the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes, when you come home at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 I expect so. I can't remember - really remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did they ever meet the teachers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Yes. All working people. From Grangetown. And all that area.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You wouldn't have any other types?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 Not at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid608221 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 You don't remember the babies dying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15285327 IS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16059240\charrsid1851734 No. I've got a slight rec - recollection - of Tommy. Very very slight but I wouldn't remember.
